Project Description
New Date Prompts for ODK-X Survey
-an Android application for performing data collection in the ODK-X
-This project is focused on adding new prompt types to capture dates and times.
-Examples of new date types: 

Add a year only input prompt type 
Add a month and year only input prompt type
Add a calendar prompt type that shows the month for a user to choose from
Add calendar prompt types for non-Gregorian calendars (e.g., Ethiopian calendar, Islamic calendar)

///PROJECT ENVIRON REQUIREMENT
1. basic system requirements for Android Studio on Windows
-Microsoft® Windows® 7/8/10 (64-bit)
-4 GB RAM minimum, 8GB RAM recommended
-2 GB of available disk space minimum,
4 GB Recommended (500 MB for IDE + 1.5 GB for Android SDK and emulator system image)
-1280 x 800 minimum screen resolution
For use with the Emulator, see the Emulator system requirements.

1b.To install Android Studio on Windows, proceed as follows:

If you downloaded an .exe file (recommended), double-click to launch it.
If you downloaded a .zip file, unpack the ZIP, copy the android-studio folder into your Program Files folder, and then open the android-studio > bin folder and launch studio64.exe (for 64-bit machines) or studio.exe (for 32-bit machines).

Follow the setup wizard in Android Studio and install any SDK packages that it recommends.

2.Android Emulator below:
-SDK Tools 26.1.1 or higher
-64-bit processor
-Windows: CPU with UG (unrestricted guest) support
-HAXM 6.2.1 or later (HAXM 7.2.0 or later recommended)


3. hardware additional requirements 
-Intel processor with support for Intel VT-x, Intel EM64T (Intel 64), and Execute Disable (XD) Bit functionality
-AMD processor on Windows: Android Studio 3.2 or higher and Windows 10 April 2018 release or higher for Windows Hypervisor Platform (WHPX) functionality
-attached webcam must have the capability to capture 720p frames.



///GITHUB REQUIREMENT
System Requirements
A computer capable of running Node.js
And capable of running Google’s Android Emulator (https://developer.android.com/studio/run/emulator#requirements), or an Android phone/tablet.

1.setting up an ODK-X environment can be found at our Developer Environment Setup wiki page
2.Install Android Studio and the SDK.
3.ODK-X Service MUST be installed on your device, whether by installing the APK or by cloning the project and deploying it.
4.Building the project
Open the Survey project in Android Studio. Select Build->Make Project to build the app.
5.Running
Be sure to install ODK-X Core onto your device before attempting to run Survey.

